00:02:04,566 --> 00:02:12,676
And Jill Fronsdale translation, one is not judge who judges a case hastily.

11
00:02:13,236 --> 00:02:16,721
A wise person considers both what is and isn't right.

12
00:02:17,883 --> 00:02:19,944
Guiding others without force

13
00:02:20,566 --> 00:02:48,717
impartially and in accord with the dharma one is called a guardian of the dharma intelligent and just so before we go into the actual verses the little story that surrounds it so it seems that some bhikkhus were returning from arms round caught in a storm they sheltered in the hall of justice at savati which is the capital of kosala king pastanadi was a great supporter of the buddha

14
00:02:51,092 --> 00:02:58,360
And they saw judges making arbitrary decisions and taking bribes and reported this to the Buddha.

15
00:02:58,561 --> 00:03:06,629
And the Buddha said, if one is influenced by monetary considerations in deciding cases, he cannot be called a just judge who abides by the law.

16
00:03:07,431 --> 00:03:15,098
If one weighs the evidence intelligently and decides a case impartially, then he is called a just judge who abides by the law.

